 I never expected my Shade DD to come into use during RvR, but just the other day, it actually did make a difference.<br>
<br>
I was in Yggdra doing solo-RvR. Later 2 groups of Hibs came to camp the Mid-entrance.<br>
<br>
So there I was, stealthed, waiting on the road for the Middies to come thru, and PA them as they run past.<br>
<br>
A kobold snuck up and one-shotted our caster, and began to sprint back to the entrance. Our archers were getting harassed by the mid's pets etc. <br>
<br>
The kobold was down to 1/3 HP, and sprinting fast, with a Firbolg on his @ss. I knew I could never catch up, so I used my DD instead. Having 196 Dex really helped, as I could chain-DD almost once per 1.5 secs. 3 DDs went in, and he slowed, allowing the Firbolg to wipe him flat.<br>
<br>
<br>
Another instance was during a keep defense. 20+ Albions were sieging our Fort, and plenty of archers below, so I couldn't ravage them safely.<br>
<br>
Climbing onto the fort wall, I targetted their healers, and chain-DDed them while they were healing. It really pissed them to no end, that their casters started to aim at me above. <br>
<br>
I jumped back down from the parapet when I got a 400+ DD burning my butts, and ran to another position, stealthed, and repeated the same thing.<br>
<br>
I'm wondering if any other Shades have found uses of their DD other than those 2 I've found.<br>
<br>
Would be great to at least help other Shades, Shade-wannabes on how to maximise the abilities (limited as they are). <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie<br>
